Elite Automotive Policy on Buying Used Cars from Customers:


Objective:
This Policy outlines the principles, procedures, and standards applied by Elite Automotive Sdn.
title: Used Car Listings for Sale of Elite Automotive:

text:
Bhd. (Elite Automotive, the Company) when purchasing used motor vehicles from individual or corporate customers (the Seller). The objective is to ensure that every vehicle acquisition is conducted transparently, ethically, and in compliance with Malaysian laws while safeguarding both parties interests. Scope:
This Policy applies exclusively to vehicles sold to Elite Automotive for direct purchase or resale purposes. It does not cover trade-ins linked to new purchases, consignment arrangements, or third-party brokerage sales, which are governed under separate policies. Eligibility to Sell:
To qualify for sale to the Company:
-Legal Ownership
The Seller must be the registered legal owner of the vehicle and must present the original JPJ registration card (Geran) or an electronic copy verified by the Road Transport Department (JPJ). Vehicles under hire-purchase financing may only be sold if the Seller discloses the outstanding balance and authorises Elite Automotive to settle it directly with the financier.

-Vehicle Category
Passenger vehicles, SUVs, MPVs, hatchbacks, and light commercial vehicles under 15 years old are generally accepted. Reconstructed, salvaged, or heavily modified vehicles are accepted only with prior management approval.

-Condition Requirements:
Vehicles must be in roadworthy condition and free from unresolved major accident damage, flood exposure, or structural alteration. The Seller must disclose the true mileage and provide service and accident history when available.

-Legal Compliance
The vehicle must be free of police cases, insurance disputes, outstanding summonses, or JPJ blacklisting. The Seller must declare any pending loans, fines, or encumbrances before inspection. Vehicle Appraisal and Valuation Process:
Preliminary Information:
The Seller shall provide:
-Make, model, and variant
-Year of manufacture and registration
-Current mileage
-Physical condition summary
-Photographs (front, rear, sides, interior, engine bay, odometer)
-Asking price and reason for sale

Approved Inspection Workshop:
All customers who wish to sell their vehicles to Elite Automotive must schedule an inspection appointment at least seven (7) working days in advance at Vissharam Supreme Workshop, located in Sentul. Address:
Vissharam Supreme Workshop
No. 27, Jalan Sentul Perdana,
Sentul Industrial Park,
51000 Kuala Lumpur,
Wilayah Persekutuan Kuala Lumpur. The workshop is managed by Mr. Vissharam, and appointments can be booked by sending a WhatsApp message to Ram at +6018-374-3947. A qualified inspector from Vissharam Supreme Workshop will perform a detailed assessment covering:
-Exterior and interior condition
-Verification of chassis and engine numbers
-Tyre wear, lighting, fluid leaks, and brake condition
-Service-book and maintenance record review
-Confirmation of accessories, spare keys, and tools
The inspection cost will be fully borne by Elite Automotive. Valuation Criteria:
The valuation is derived from:
-Current Malaysian market pricing and industry trade-value data
-Condition and mileage relative to model year
-Cost of reconditioning, refurbishment, and certification
-Brand demand and resale probability
The Company issues a written purchase offer valid for seven (7) calendar days from the inspection date. Offer Acceptance and Documentation:
Upon Seller acceptance of the offer:
A Vehicle Sale Agreement is executed, detailing price, payment mode, and transfer obligations.
title: Bhd. (Elite Automotive, the Company) when purchasing used motor ve

text:
Supporting documents required:
-Original JPJ registration card
-Sellers NRIC copy
-Hire-purchase settlement letter (if applicable)
-Completed JPJ K3 / e-Auto Transfer form
-Elite Automotive will retain digital copies for compliance and audit purposes. Once signed, both parties are legally bound by the terms of sale. Payment Procedures:
Payment Method:
-Payment is made via bank transfer, bank draft, or cashiers order only after verification of documents.
-No cash transactions exceeding Bank Negara Malaysia regulatory limits will be accepted. Timeline:
-Payments are processed within three (3) working days after all documents are verified and the vehicle is delivered to the Company. Loan Settlement (if applicable):
-Where the vehicle is under hire-purchase, the Company shall directly pay the financier the settlement amount and pay any remaining balance to the Seller.
-Confirmation letters from the financier will be kept as proof of settlement. Receipt Issuance:
-A digital or printed receipt showing purchase price, payment method, and date will be issued immediately after payment. Ownership Transfer:
Transfer Responsibility:
-Elite Automotive manages the ownership transfer through JPJs e-Auto system or authorised runner.
-The Seller must provide full cooperation in signing all transfer forms promptly. Effective Date of Transfer:
-Liability for road offences, traffic summonses, and accidents ceases on the date both parties sign the sale agreement and hand over the vehicle.
-Any offence committed prior to that date remains the Sellers responsibility. Notification to Authorities:
-Where necessary, Elite Automotive may notify JPJ and the insurance provider to confirm transfer completion. Representations and Warranties by Seller:
By selling to the Company, the Seller warrants that:
-The vehicle description and condition declared are true and accurate.
-The odometer has not been tampered with.
-The vehicle is not stolen, cloned, or subject to any court proceedings.
-There are no undisclosed accident or insurance claims pending.
-The Seller possesses full authority to sell and transfer ownership. Elite Automotive reserves the right to rescind the agreement, adjust valuation, or seek recovery if post-sale verification reveals material misrepresentation. Vehicle Condition at Handover:
-The vehicle shall be delivered in the same condition as inspected.
-All personal belongings must be removed prior to handover.
-The Company is not responsible for items left in the vehicle after collection.
-Any missing component that was present during inspection may result in a price adjustment or deduction. Cancellation of Sale:
-The Seller may cancel before signing the Vehicle Sale Agreement without penalty.
-Once documents are signed and payment initiated, cancellation is not permitted.
-In cases where inspection fees, transportation, or administrative costs have been incurred, such expenses may be deducted from any refundable amount if the Seller withdraws prematurely.
-If Elite Automotive elects to cancel (e.g., due to failed ownership verification or adverse findings), any deposit or partial payment received will be refunded within fourteen (14) business days. Confidentiality and Data Protection:
-Elite Automotive complies with the Personal Data Protection Act 2010 (PDPA).
-Seller informationincluding identification documents, photographs, and financial detailsis used solely for transaction and regulatory purposes.
-Access to personal data is restricted to authorised personnel, and data is stored in secure systems with audit tracking.
title: Supporting documents required:

text:
Compliance with Law:
All purchases shall adhere to:
-Road Transport Act 1987
-Hire-Purchase Act 1967
-Consumer Protection Act 1999
-Companies Act 2016
-Any other applicable Malaysian statutes, JPJ directives, and Bank Negara Malaysia guidelines on financial transactions. Elite Automotive shall cooperate fully with law enforcement or regulatory agencies for verification or investigation related to any purchased vehicle. Roles and Responsibilities:
Company Management:
-Approves policy revisions and ensures compliance.
-Oversees large-value purchases exceeding authorised consultant limits. Sales and Customer Service Department:
-Administers inspections, valuations, and documentation.
-Ensures consistent pricing methodology across all branches. Inspectors and Consultants:
-Collect accurate information and complete the inspection checklist.
-Report suspicious cases (e.g., tampered chassis, fake documents) immediately to management. Finance Department:
-Processes payments and maintains transaction records.
-Reconciles bank settlements and prepares statutory reporting. Record Keeping:
-All agreements, valuations, inspection reports, and payment receipts are archived for seven (7) years in both physical and digital form.
-Records may be accessed for internal audits, tax filing, or regulatory reviews. Risk and Fraud Prevention
-Elite Automotive employs verification measures to detect cloned vehicles or falsified documents.
-Any suspected fraudulent activity will be reported to the Royal Malaysia Police (PDRM) and JPJ.
-Transactions involving unusually low or high declared values may be subject to additional scrutiny and management approval. Limitation of Liability:
The Companys liability in any transaction is limited strictly to the purchase price stated in the Vehicle Sale Agreement. Elite Automotive shall not be responsible for:
-Market value fluctuations after offer acceptance, or
-Consequential loss suffered by the Seller for any reason unrelated to breach by the Company. Amendments and Review:
This Policy shall be reviewed annually or whenever there is a significant change in law or business operations. Any amendment must be approved by the Board of Directors and communicated to all staff in writing. Contact Information:

By proceeding with the sale of a used vehicle to Elite Automotive, the Seller acknowledges having read, understood, and agreed to comply with all terms of this Policy on Buying Used Cars from Customers. Elite Automotive Trade-In Policy:


Objective:
This Policy establishes the principles, procedures, and compliance standards applied by Elite Automotive Sdn. Bhd. (Elite Automotive, the Company) when accepting vehicles as trade-ins from customers purchasing another vehicle from the Company. The objective of this Policy is to ensure that every trade-in transaction is conducted transparently, fairly, and in accordance with applicable Malaysian laws, while protecting the interests of both the Company and its customers. Scope:
This Policy applies to all trade-in transactions where:
-A customer offers their owned vehicle as part payment toward the purchase of another vehicle from Elite Automotive; and
-The Company agrees to accept such vehicle for valuation, inspection, and offset against the purchase price of a replacement vehicle.
title: Compliance with Law:

text:
This Policy does not apply to:
-Direct vehicle purchases without trade-in, which are governed under the Policy on Buying Used Cars from Customers; or
-Vehicles sold under consignment or third-party sale arrangements. Eligibility Requirements:
To qualify for trade-in consideration, the following requirements must be met:

Ownership:
-The customer must be the registered legal owner of the vehicle and possess the original JPJ registration card (Geran).
-Vehicles under financing must have the outstanding balance declared. The Company may, with written consent, settle the remaining loan directly with the financier. Vehicle Type and Age:
-Accepted categories include passenger cars, SUVs, MPVs, and light commercial vehicles.
-Vehicles older than 15 years or in unroadworthy condition may be declined or accepted only with management approval. Condition:
-Vehicles must be in a condition suitable for resale and free from flood damage, major structural repairs, or tampering.
-The customer must disclose known defects, prior accidents, or pending insurance claims. Legal Compliance:
-The vehicle must not be subject to ongoing investigations, outstanding summonses, or JPJ blacklisting.
-The customer must declare any lien, encumbrance, or outstanding loan obligation. Definition of Trade-In:
A trade-in is a transaction in which a customer transfers ownership of their existing vehicle to Elite Automotive in exchange for a Trade-In Value, which is offset against the price of another vehicle purchased from the Company. The Trade-In Value is determined following vehicle inspection, appraisal, and market evaluation conducted by the Company. Vehicle Appraisal and Valuation Process:
Information Collection:
The customer shall provide:
-Vehicle make, model, and variant
-Year of manufacture and registration
-Current mileage (approximate acceptable)
-Overall physical and mechanical condition
-Photographs of exterior, interior, odometer, and engine bay
-Declaration of ownership status, outstanding loan, and reason for trade-in

Inspection:
The Company or its appointed inspector will conduct a detailed vehicle inspection, which includes:
-Physical verification of chassis and engine numbers
-Evaluation of interior and exterior condition
-Functional check of major components (engine, transmission, brakes, lights, tyres)
-Review of service records and accident history
An inspection report will be documented and signed by the Companys representative. Valuation Criteria:
Valuation will be based on:
-Current Malaysian used car market rates
-Vehicle age, mileage, and condition
-Reconditioning and preparation costs
-Model demand and resale potential
The Company will issue a written Trade-In Offer, valid for seven (7) calendar days from the date of inspection. Trade-In Agreement:
Upon acceptance of the offer, both parties shall execute a Trade-In Agreement, which will include:
-Details of the trade-in vehicle (brand, model, registration number, chassis number)
-The agreed Trade-In Value
-Details of the new vehicle being purchased
-The remaining balance to be paid by the customer (if any)
-Terms relating to ownership transfer and liability
-Acknowledgement of the vehicles condition as inspected
The Trade-In Agreement shall form part of the overall Vehicle Sales Order for the replacement vehicle. Financial Settlement
Offset Mechanism:
-The Trade-In Value shall be applied as a credit against the total purchase price of the new vehicle.
-The customer shall pay or finance the remaining balance, if applicable.
title: This Policy does not apply to:

text:
Excess Value:
-If the Trade-In Value exceeds the price of the vehicle purchased, the Company shall pay the difference to the customer within five (5) working days following completion of ownership transfer. Loan Settlement:
-Where the trade-in vehicle is under a financing arrangement, the Company shall settle the outstanding balance with the financier and pay the remaining amount (if any) to the customer. Receipts and Acknowledgements:
The Company shall issue receipts for all financial transactions related to trade-in and settlement. Ownership Transfer:
Transfer Responsibility:
-Upon signing the Trade-In Agreement, the customer authorises Elite Automotive to initiate the ownership transfer process via the JPJ e-Auto system.
-The customer must provide the necessary documents, including the original registration card, NRIC copy, and loan release letter (if applicable). Effective Transfer Date:
-The customers liability for summonses, fines, or accidents ends on the date of signing the Trade-In Agreement and delivery of the vehicle to the Company.
-Any offence prior to that date remains the customers responsibility. Handover Requirements:
-Vehicles must be delivered with all keys, remote controls, toolkits, and service manuals.
-Vehicles must remain in the same condition as inspected. Any change in condition before handover may lead to revaluation. Incomplete Transfer:
-If required documentation is not provided within ten (10) working days, the Company reserves the right to delay delivery of the replacement vehicle or cancel the trade-in transaction. Vehicle Condition at Handover:
-The vehicle must be in the same state as when inspected.
-Personal items must be removed prior to handover.
-Elite Automotive will not be responsible for loss of belongings left in the vehicle.
-If missing components or damage are identified upon handover, the Company reserves the right to adjust the agreed value or withdraw the trade-in offer. Warranties and Representations:
The customer represents and warrants that:
-The information provided regarding the trade-in vehicle is true and accurate.
-The odometer reading reflects genuine mileage.
-The vehicle is not stolen, cloned, or under legal dispute.
-All loans, summonses, and encumbrances have been declared. Elite Automotive reserves the right to revise or cancel the trade-in transaction if material misrepresentation is discovered before ownership transfer is completed. Cancellation:
Customer-Initiated Cancellation:
-If the customer cancels the purchase of the new vehicle after executing the Trade-In Agreement, the trade-in arrangement shall be automatically void.
-The Company may, at its discretion, offer to buy the vehicle under the Policy on Buying Used Cars from Customers.
-Any payment or deposit already made will be handled according to the Deposits, Refunds and Cancellation Policy. Company-Initiated Cancellation:
-The Company may cancel a trade-in transaction if inspection or verification reveals hidden defects, falsified documents, or outstanding legal issues.
-In such cases, the vehicle will be returned if ownership has not been transferred, or the trade-in amount refunded if payment has been made. Refund Processing:
-Any refund payable under this clause shall be completed within fourteen (14) business days. Confidentiality and Data Protection:
All personal and vehicle information collected during the trade-in process shall be handled in accordance with the Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA) 2010. The data shall be used solely for transaction, verification, and regulatory purposes and shall not be disclosed to unauthorised third parties.

Sales & Customer Service Department:

-Approves exceptions, large-value trade-ins, and resolves escalated disputes. All employees are required to comply with this Policy and maintain transparency throughout the trade-in process. Risk and Fraud Prevention:
-Elite Automotive conducts verification of chassis and engine numbers, JPJ records, and police databases to prevent acquisition of stolen or cloned vehicles.
-Any suspicious documentation or ownership irregularity shall be escalated to management immediately.

All documents related to trade-in transactionsincluding inspection reports, valuation forms, agreements, and settlement receiptsshall be retained for seven (7) years in both digital and physical format for audit and legal purposes. Records are stored securely and accessible only to authorised personnel. Limitation of Liability:
Elite Automotives total liability arising out of a trade-in transaction shall be limited to the Trade-In Value agreed upon in the Trade-In Agreement. The Company shall not be responsible for:
-Changes in market resale prices after completion of the transaction; or
-Losses arising from financing rejection, documentation delay, or customers failure to fulfil transfer obligations. Compliance with Law:
All trade-in activities are governed by and must comply with:
-The Road Transport Act 1987
-The Hire-Purchase Act 1967
-The Contracts Act 1950
-The Consumer Protection Act 1999
-The Personal Data Protection Act 2010

Elite Automotive shall cooperate fully with regulatory and enforcement bodies as required under Malaysian law. Review and Amendment:

Objective:
This Policy establishes the official framework by which Elite Automotive Sdn. Bhd. (Elite Automotive, the Company) manages all matters relating to customer deposits, refunds, and cancellations for vehicle purchases, bookings, and trade-in transactions. The purpose of this Policy is to ensure that all monetary transactions are handled with fairness, transparency, and accountability, in accordance with Malaysian contract law, consumer protection statutes, and internal governance standards. Scope:
This Policy applies to:
-All customers placing booking deposits or purchase deposits for vehicles with Elite Automotive;
-All customers involved in trade-in transactions that include advance payments or deposit transfers; and
-All cancellations, whether initiated by the customer or by the Company, prior to delivery or completion of ownership transfer.
title: Roles and Responsibilities:

text:
This Policy does not apply to vehicles sold under consignment, auction, fleet liquidation, or any third-party partnership arrangement, which are governed under separate agreements. Definitions:
-Customer means any individual or business entity who reserves, purchases, or trades in a vehicle with the Company.
-Booking Deposit means a partial payment made by a Customer to reserve a specific vehicle for a fixed period pending full payment or loan approval.
-Purchase Deposit means any sum paid as part of the purchase price after a booking has been confirmed.
-Refund means the return of money paid by a Customer under specific conditions outlined in this Policy.
-Cancellation means any withdrawal, termination, or revocation of a booking, purchase, or trade-in transaction before completion of delivery or full payment, initiated by either the Customer or the Company. Cancellation is deemed effective on the date written notice is received by the Company.
-Trade-In Value means the value assigned to a vehicle that a Customer offers as part payment toward another vehicle.
-Effective Date means the date this Policy is approved by the Board of Directors. Deposit Acceptance and Handling Procedures:
Deposit Amounts:
-The standard Booking Deposit ranges from RM500 to RM5,000, depending on vehicle type, model, and market value.
-Higher deposits may be required for premium or limited-edition vehicles, subject to written agreement.
-All deposits must be accompanied by an official Booking Form or Offer to Purchase Agreement, duly signed by both parties. Payment Methods:
Deposits must be paid to the Companys official business account via:
-Online bank transfer;
-Debit or credit card; or
-Bank draft or cashiers order. Cash payments exceeding RM5,000 are strictly prohibited under the Anti-Money Laundering and Anti-Terrorism Financing Act 2001 (AMLA). Receipt and Recordkeeping
-Every deposit must be acknowledged by an official Company Receipt, stating the payers full name, NRIC, vehicle registration or chassis number (where applicable), and payment amount.
-Copies of all receipts and forms are retained digitally for seven (7) years in compliance with Companies Act 2016 audit requirements. Purpose and Validity of Deposits:
-Deposits serve as proof of the Customers intent to proceed with the purchase and the Companys commitment to reserve the vehicle.
-Vehicles will be reserved for seven (7) calendar days from the date of deposit unless otherwise stated in writing.
-If the Customer fails to complete documentation, financing, or payment within this period, the Company reserves the right to cancel the booking and forfeit the deposit. Refund Eligibility and Non-Eligibility:
Refundable Deposits:
A deposit shall be refunded in full where:
-The vehicle is withdrawn by the Company due to stock unavailability or damage discovered before delivery;
-Ownership or legal transfer issues prevent the sale;
-The Customers hire-purchase loan is rejected by two (2) licensed banks, supported by official rejection letters;
-The Company cancels the transaction due to compliance, documentation, or fraud-prevention issues not attributable to the Customer. Refunds under these conditions shall be processed within fourteen (14) business days from the date of written confirmation.
title: This Policy does not apply to vehicles sold under consignment, auction

text:
Non-Refundable Deposits:
Deposits are automatically forfeited when:
-The Customer unilaterally cancels the transaction after deposit payment;
-The Customer fails to submit necessary documentation or loan applications within the reservation period;
-The Customer withdraws after loan approval;
-The Customer delays full payment beyond agreed deadlines;
-The Customer provides false or misleading information;
-The Customer fails to attend scheduled collection without notice. 6.3 Partial Refunds (Discretionary)
Management may, at its sole discretion, refund up to 50% of the deposit where:
-The cancellation arises from unavoidable financial hardship, supported by documentation;
-Loan rejection occurs after the reservation period but before signing; or
-The Customer wishes to transfer the deposit to another available vehicle under the Companys inventory. Such discretionary refunds must be approved in writing by the Head of Sales and verified by the Finance Department. Cancellations:
Customer-Initiated Cancellation:
-Customers must submit cancellations in writing, via email or WhatsApp message to the assigned sales consultant or official company contact.
-Verbal or phone cancellations are not legally valid until confirmed in writing.
-The effective date of cancellation shall be the date the Company acknowledges receipt of written notice.
-Once cancellation is confirmed, refund or forfeiture terms apply as per Section 6. Company-Initiated Cancellation:
Elite Automotive reserves the right to cancel any booking or purchase agreement if:
-Fraud, misrepresentation, or illegal activity is suspected;
-Vehicle is damaged, stolen, or rendered untransferable prior to sale;
-Regulatory or financing non-compliance is detected; or
-Management deems continuation of the transaction contrary to company policy or law. In such cases, any deposit paid will be refunded in full within fourteen (14) business days. Refund Procedures:
-All refund requests must be accompanied by a signed Refund Request Form and proof of payment.
-Refunds will be made by bank transfer to the original payers account only.
-Processing time:
-Standard refunds: 14 business days
-Exceptional or trade-in-linked refunds: up to 21 business days
-Refund approvals require two management signatories: Head of Sales and Finance Manager.
-The Customer will receive a Refund Acknowledgment Receipt upon completion. Trade-In Related Deposits:
-Where a trade-in vehicle forms part of a purchase, the trade-in value will be credited toward the final invoice amount.
-If the Customer cancels after inspection but before completion, any deposit paid may be forfeited unless cancellation is due to loan rejection or company withdrawal.
-Where a trade-in vehicle has already been collected, cancellation is not permissible, and the transaction will proceed under the agreed valuation terms. Refund Exclusions:
No refund shall be granted for:
-Administrative fees, inspection charges, or JPJ-related processing costs;
-Insurance or road tax renewal fees already paid on the Customers behalf;
-Any government or third-party service fees incurred prior to cancellation. Documentation and Record Retention:
-The Finance Department shall maintain detailed logs of all deposits, refunds, cancellations, and approvals.
-All supporting documentation (agreements, receipts, bank slips, email correspondence) shall be retained for seven (7) years for legal and audit purposes.

Confidentiality and Data Protection
All Customer data collected under this Policy is protected under the Personal Data Protection Act 2010 (PDPA).
-Information shall only be used for transaction and compliance purposes.
-Access is limited to authorised personnel from Sales, Finance, and Management teams. Roles and Responsibilities:
Sales Consultant: 
Explain deposit terms to Customer, collect deposit, and issue official receipt. Finance Department:
Process and record payments, validate refund claims, ensure AMLA compliance. Customer Service:
Communicate cancellation status and coordinate refund logistics. Management:
Approve exceptions, oversee policy enforcement, and handle dispute resolution. Dispute Resolution:
In the event of disagreement regarding refund or forfeiture:
-The Customer shall first submit a written appeal to Management.
-If unresolved, the matter may be referred to the Tribunal for Consumer Claims Malaysia (TTPM) or KPDN under the Consumer Protection Act 1999.
-The Company reserves the right to defend its position with full documentary evidence of policy compliance. Limitation of Liability:
The Companys liability is strictly limited to the amount of the deposit paid. Elite Automotive shall not be liable for consequential or indirect losses arising from:
-Loan rejections;
-Third-party financing delays;
-Customer failure to comply with documentation or timelines. Legal Compliance:
This Policy shall be interpreted and enforced in accordance with:
-Contracts Act 1950
-Consumer Protection Act 1999
-Hire-Purchase Act 1967
-Companies Act 2016
-Anti-Money Laundering and Anti-Terrorism Financing Act 2001 (AMLA)
-Personal Data Protection Act 2010 (PDPA)


Policy Review and Amendment
-This Policy shall be reviewed annually or when changes occur in law, business structure, or regulatory guidelines.
-All amendments require written approval by the Board of Directors and must be communicated to all departments. Contact Information:
